How much can you earn without paying tax and National Insurance?
Income Tax (TULOVERO)
Everyone can earn a certain amount each year without paying any Income Tax. This is called your Personal Allowance. In 2011-12 the Personal Allowance is £7,475. 
National Insurance (Sairasvakuutus, eläke yms)
You can earn up to £139 a week (2011-12) before you pay any National Insurance contributions.
